ctions and\na Lojasiewicz distance inequality for the Yang-Mills energy function. A special\ncase of our estimate, when $X$ has dimension four and the connection $A$ is\nanti-self-dual, was proved by Fukaya (1998) by entirely different methods.\nLastly, we prove that if $A$ is a smooth Yang-Mills connection with small\nenough energy, then $A$ is necessarily flat.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Jun 2019 12:58:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 1 Jul 2019 17:28:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-02"}
